Amcu agreed to take a 5.5% pay rise for the first year and 5.5% or the consumer inflation rate, whichever is the greater, in years two and three. WESTONARIA, South Africa - The Association of Mineworkers and Construction Union (Amcu) has agreed to a wage settlement with Sibanye-Stillwater on Wednesday, ending a five-month strike that has hit gold production and earnings. Amcu agreed to take a 5.5% pay rise for the first year and 5.5% or the consumer inflation rate, whichever is the greater, in years two and three, Sibanye said in a statement